cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses workload scheduling in a Private Cloud platform, which involves distributed and parallel computing. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper discusses the development of a software utility for energy measurement and workload classification. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses the development of a power model for predicting server energy consumption. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper mentions the effect of network resource consumption on server power consumption. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is another possible category as the paper discusses the impact of workload characteristics on server power consumption and proposes a solution for efficient workload scheduling.
